  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@vvo, where you suggesting something like?\n- `require('foo')`: load global module `foo`\n- `require('./foo'): load local module in`./foo/index.js`\n- `require('./foo.js'): load local module in`./foo.js`\n\nIf so, I like the idea, to easily spot where we're requiring from, and make the magic more explicit. I'm not sure there is much convention agreed on that point in the community, and thus is an eslint rule exists. If no such rule exist, we should at least agree on the way to go and note it in the `CONTRIBUTING` so it is explicit.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-12-02T21:18:18Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/710#issuecomment-161436668",
