  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Because that's the easiest way to tell if the `require` was legitimate or not. Furthermore, if I didn't, files like `Object.freeze.js` would be detected as valid with `require(Object.freeze)`. (With webpack you can require almost any file extension so I didn't want it to be restrictive, so it accepts any file with a dot in its filename as valid -- except if it doesn't exist)\n",
